Project Overview
The User Authentication System is a Java Full Stack end‑to‑end web application designed to provide secure Login and Logout functionality for users. This project demonstrates the integration of frontend technologies (HTML & CSS), backend development using Java, Oracle database for data persistence, and Selenium automation testing for validating application behavior.
The system ensures that only authenticated users can access protected areas of the application and provides a secure logout mechanism to terminate user sessions. This project follows industry‑standard practices and is suitable for academic, training, and real‑world enterprise‑level applications.

Objectives of the Project

To design a user‑friendly Login and Logout interface
To implement secure authentication logic using Java
To store and validate user credentials using an Oracle database
To ensure data integrity and session management
To automate functional testing using Selenium WebDriver
To demonstrate complete end‑to‑end full stack development


