Functional Description
1. Login Functionality

The user enters a username and password on the login page.
The credentials are sent to the backend server.
The backend validates the credentials against records stored in the Oracle database.
If valid, the user is redirected to the Dashboard/Home page.
If invalid, an error message is displayed.

2. Logout Functionality

The logged‑in user can click the Logout button.
The session is invalidated on the server.
The user is redirected back to the Login page.
This ensures secure termination of the session.


